All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Nominal, LF, Indexed, Mutable, Unifiable, Variable
public class NominalVar
extends HyloVar
implements Nominal

A class for variables over NominalAtom objects. Nominal vars take precedence over generic hylo vars. Types are unified with other hylo vars and nominal atoms.

unify

public Object unify(Object u,
                    Substitution sub)
             throws UnifyFailure
Description copied from class: HyloFormula
Unify this Unfiable with another Object. This default implementation will reverse the direction of unification for a variable, otherwise it fails. NB: The implementation of unification in the hylo package is not complete; a particular limitation is that no attempt is made to unify lists of terms connected by an Op instance.

Specified by:
unify in interface Unifiable
Overrides:
unify in class HyloVar
sub - Substitution containing the variable resolutions
Returns:
an object which represents the unification of this Unifiable with the Object
Throws:
UnifyFailure - if this Unifiable cannot be unified with the Object
